import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Privacy Policy" 
  description="Standard business privacy policy for the Maine Dispensary Guide. We protect our community of cannabis entrepreneurs and founders." 
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1511497584788-876760111969?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1200&h=400"
  article={{ author: "Maine Dispensary Guide Editorial Team", publishDate: "2026-01-01", modifiedDate: "2026-04-04", section: "Legal" }}
>
  <article class="legal-page">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="last-updated">Last Updated: March 23, 2026</p>

    <section>
      <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
      <p>This Privacy Policy describes how the Maine Dispensary Guide collects, uses, and shares your personal information when you visit our site or use our resources. We are committed to protecting your professional data and ensuring transparency in our operations.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>2. Information Collection</h2>
      <p>We collect information you provide directly (name, business email, project details) and technical data (IP address, browser type) to improve our guides and connect you with verified Maine cannabis professionals.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>3. Data Usage & Sharing</h2>
      <p>Your data is used to provide technical updates, research-grade guides, and professional introductions. We do not sell your personal data. We only share information with third-party service providers (lawyers, CPAs) when you explicitly request an introduction.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>4. Security</h2>
      <p>We implement robust security measures to safeguard your information from unauthorized access. As a technical hub for Maine's cannabis industry, we prioritize the integrity of our founder network.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>5. Cookies & Tracking</h2>
      <p>We use essential cookies to maintain site functionality and user sessions. Analytics cookies help us understand how visitors navigate our guide library so we can improve content organization. We do not use advertising cookies or third-party tracking pixels. All analytics data is aggregated and anonymized before review.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>6. User Rights Under Maine Law</h2>
      <p>Maine residents have the right to request a copy of their personal data, request corrections to inaccurate information, and request deletion of their personal data where applicable. As a business-to-business platform serving cannabis entrepreneurs, we retain minimal personal data and only for as long as necessary to provide our services.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>7. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>We retain form submission data for 24 months to follow up on resource inquiries. Technical logs are retained for 90 days. Financial records related to any transactions are retained for 7 years per Maine cannabis regulatory requirements. After these periods, data is permanently deleted from our servers and backup systems.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>8. Third-Party Links</h2>
      <p>Our guides may include links to external resources including Maine Office of Cannabis Policy, the Metrc compliance system, and municipal planning departments. These external sites operate under their own privacy policies. We encourage users to review those policies before submitting any personal information.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>9. Policy Updates</h2>
      <p>We update this Privacy Policy annually or when significant changes occur in Maine cannabis regulations. Material changes will be communicated via a notice on our homepage. The "Last Updated" date at the top of this page reflects the most recent revision.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>10. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>If you have questions regarding this policy or your data rights, please reach out to <a href="mailto:admin@mainedispensaryguide.com">admin@mainedispensaryguide.com</a>. For urgent matters related to data breaches or security incidents, please include "SECURITY" in your email subject line for priority handling.</p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

